This model is the most finicky. It doesn't drive well at all while it's accelerating, so you have to really prep it up on a straight road before you let the car loose on a corner. But when you do, it does really clean laps.
It just doesn't do corners very well. You have to give it a very good start in order for it to make a clean lap, but it crashes constantly.

Perfect laps, wow. It didn't crash nor scrape the wall at all from speeds 11.8s/lap to 13.5s/lap.

Worse performance than in 0ms implemented lag. It has to be driven slower in order to account for the fact that it starts turning later and it makes mistakes when donkeycar skips frames in unfortunate places.

At lower speeds, it started to turn corners too early, but at higher speeds, it just didn't manage corners at certain fast moments (like in the U-corner) and the lag caused it to skip frames. A poor driver all around.
It managed clean laps whenever the speed was great, although it sometimes didn't steer enough when entering into the snake corner and crashed straight into the sunny wall.

Microadjustments to the course of the car are the bane of laggy models' existence. It constantly crashed either into the sunny corner or into the wall before the left L-corner. Sometimes it could drive really beautifully though, just like an FS1 model without any implemented lag.
No clean laps. It doesn't know what to do when it's headed for a wall. The frameshift causes it to think it should go forward when faced with a wall.
